reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It seems very durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It's ok- Just ok
reviews.reviewText: I have used this cushion in my office chair at home because my chair doesn't have much cushion or give. The cushion definitely helps with some of the problems I was experiencing with discomfort in certain areas. However it is not the best, and could be designed better.The pros--My butt doesn't get too hot as this thing has decent airflow. The cover is breathable and the grid allows for breathing.-It does help with cushioning a little.-It has held up for the past year and looks and functions like newThe cons-I weigh 200lbs and its to thin to provide the support I really need. For shorter usages its fine, but after 8 hours in the chair, there are some hot spots.-It slides around on my seat. It has little grip beads in the material but they don't stop it from moving, so I have to adjust it several times a day to keep it in place.- It's too narrow for my body. another inch or two would be betterI will continue to use it for a few more months, but if I were to do it over again, I would spend a bit more and get a thicker, higher quality cushion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Metal bleacher comfort
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for sitting on the metal bleachers at softball/football games. The size is good and the comfort is excellent, watched a double header and the cushion did not fail. The cushion is a gel that is very comfortable that comes with a cover and a carrying case. The case is ok it’s just a piece of plastic but the cover seems durable and has raised dots to help prevent the cushion from sliding. I would recommend this product without hesitation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This cushion has been my lifeline. I have disintegrating slipped disc that has periods where it just feels like bone is grinding against bone. Before I got this cushion taking public transportation was an ongoing exercise in torture.This cushion absorbs the impact from potholes and speed humps like a champ. The fact that it is so easily folded and put in my bag makes it indispensable to me. I used to be terrified to sit down but this cushion has changed that for good.
